library(tidyverse)
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.3.0 
##  ggplot2 3.2.1      purrr   0.3.3
##  tibble  2.1.3      dplyr   0.8.4
##  tidyr   1.0.2      stringr 1.4.0
##  readr   1.3.1      forcats 0.4.0
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
## x dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
## x dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
library(ggplot2)
SNPs<- read.table("23andMe_complete.txt", header = TRUE, sep = "\t")

Exercise 1:

ggplot(data = SNPs) +
  stat_count(mapping = aes(chromosome))

Exercise 2

SNPs$chromosome = ordered(SNPs$chromosome, levels=c(seq(1, 22), "X", "Y", "MT"))
ggplot(data = SNPs) +
  stat_count(mapping = aes(SNPs$chromosome))

Exercise 3

ggplot(data = SNPs) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(chromosome, fill = genotype))

Exercise 4

ggplot(data = SNPs) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(chromosome, fill = genotype), position = "fill")

Exercise 5

ggplot(data = SNPs) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(chromosome, fill = genotype), position = "dodge")

Exercise 6

ggplot(data = SNPs) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(chromosome, fill = genotype), position = "dodge") +
  facet_wrap(~genotype)
